<TITLE> Maldives president says accepts defeat: state radio </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MALE, Oct 29 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Maldives' president for the past three decades said Wednesday he accepted his defeat in a historic runoff poll to an opposition candidate he had jailed repeatedly during his tenure as Asia's longest-serving leader. "Beloved citizens of the Maldives, I accept the results of the October 28 runoff election and respectfully congratulate Mohamed Nasheed and his party," President Maumoon Abdul Gayoom told the state-run Voice of Maldives radio. He said he would not leave the country
